SIMPLE: wang
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Wang
<hw>Wang</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>wange</ets>,
AS. <ets>wange</ets>, <ets>wonge</ets>, cheek, jaw; akin to D.
<ets>wang</ets>, OS. & OHG. <ets>wanga</ets>, G.
<ets>wange</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>The jaw, jawbone, or cheek bone.</def> <mark>[Obs.
or Prov. Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>So work aye the <qex>wangs</qex> in his head.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A slap; a blow.</def> <mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark>
<rj><au>Halliwell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Wang tooth</b></col>, <cd>a cheek tooth; a molar.</cd>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wang</ent>⟦br⟧

